 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/fish-ingredients-800x1200.png 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/fish-ingredients-600x900.png 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/fish-ingredients-260x390.png 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/fish-ingredients-150x225.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLemon Juice and Olive Oil\u003c/strong\u003e are the base of the sauce.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAromatics\u003c/strong\u003e: Red onion and garlic\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOlives and Capers \u003c/strong\u003egive the chimichurri a briny, tangy flavor. Use any kind of green olive, like manzanilla or Castelvetrano.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSeasoning: \u003c/strong\u003eSalt, black pepper, crushed red pepper\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHerbs:\u003c/strong\u003e Dried oregano and fresh parsley\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhite Fish Fillets: \u003c/strong\u003eYou can use any white fish, such as branzino, red snapper, or halibut.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePantry Staples for the Fish:\u003c/strong\u003e Season the fish with salt and pepper, and use olive oil to prevent the fillets from sticking in the skillet.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eHow to Pan Sear Fish\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis easy olive chimichurri and fish recipe is low effort, high reward. Just chop and mix the sauce ingredients, and cook the fish in less than 10 minutes! \u003cstrong\u003eSee the recipe card at the bottom for printable directions\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"550\" height=\"825\" data-id=\"143261\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-550x825.jpg\" alt=\"Olive Chimichurri\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-2-1.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eMake the olive chimichurri.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"550\" height=\"825\" data-id=\"143258\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-550x825.jpg\" alt=\"Pan Seared Fish\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-4-1.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePan sear the fish.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"550\" height=\"825\" data-id=\"143262\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-550x825.jpg\" alt=\"spoon olive chimichurri over fish\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-5-1.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eSpoon chimichurri over the fish and enjoy!\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFirst Make The Chimichurri: \u003c/strong\u003eMix all the ingredients in a bowl.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSeason the fish\u003c/strong\u003e with salt and pepper.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSear the Fish:\u003c/strong\u003e Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place the fillets skin-side down and cook for 5 minutes. Flip over and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eVariations\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAcid: \u003c/strong\u003eSwap lemon juice with red or white wine vinegar.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDon’t like olives? \u003c/strong\u003eSkip them.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFish: \u003c/strong\u003eUse any white fish available to you. I always choose what’s freshest or local.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-pin-description=\"This Pan-Seared Fish with Olive Chimichurri can be made with any white fish. The olive chimichurri is so flavorful and beautifully complements the fish! #fish #lentenrecipes #pescatarian #seafood #mediterraneandiet #dairyfree #glutenfree #dinner #olives\" data-pin-title=\"Pan Seared Fish with Olive Chimichurri\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1.jpg\" alt=\"olive chimichurri\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-3-1-150x225.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eHow do you get the bitterness out of chimichurri?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo ensure the chimichurri doesn’t taste bitter, make sure your parsley is fresh and don’t use any thick stems. It’s also best to chop by hand rather than use a food processor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eServing Suggestions for Pan Seared Fish\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis pan seared fish would be great with a salad or roasted vegetables. Here’s some ideas:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVegetables: \u003c/strong\u003eServe the fish with an \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/arugula-salad/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003earugula salad\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/chopped-feta-salad/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003echopped feta salad\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/roasted-asparagus-0-pts/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003eroasted asparagus\u003c/a\u003e, or air fryer \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/air-fryer-radishes/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003eradishes\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStarchy Sides: \u003c/strong\u003ePair it with \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/lemon-parsley-potato-foil-packets/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003elemon-parsley potatoes\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/greek-orzo-salad/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003eGreek orzo salad\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/lentil-salad/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003elental salad\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/chickpea-salad/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003echickpea salad\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-pin-description=\"This Pan-Seared Fish with Olive Chimichurri can be made with any white fish. The olive chimichurri is so flavorful and beautifully complements the fish! #fish #lentenrecipes #pescatarian #seafood #mediterraneandiet #dairyfree #glutenfree #dinner #olives\" data-pin-title=\"Pan Seared Fish with Olive Chimichurri\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1.jpg\" alt=\"Pan Seared Fish with Olive Chimichurri\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Pan-Seared-Fish-with-Olive-Chimichurri-6-1-150x225.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eStorage\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMake Ahead: \u003c/strong\u003ePrepare the chimichurri 1 day early, if needed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRefrigerate \u003c/strong\u003ethe fish and sauce up to 3 days.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRoom-Temp Sauce:\u003c/strong\u003e Let it sit on the counter before eating to bring it back to room temperature.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-pin-description=\"This Pan-Seared Fish with Olive Chimichurri can be made with any white fish. The olive chimichurri is so flavorful and beautifully compl